            "id": 5320,
            "user": {
                "id": 140,
                "name": "Spyhawk"
            },
            "notes": "Distance is still a factor to consider here. Now the name doesn't disappear right away on long distance (as it should), but currently on short distance the name doesn't show at all (as this is the way SD implemented it) but the name *appears* when you look away.\r\n\r\nHere we can either:\r\n1/ remove the short distance trick and make disguised name appears at all time. This will make it easier for covops to sneak undercover.\r\n2/ keep it as it is in vanilla. Disguised name doesn't appear at all on short distance.\r\n3/ keep it as it is. This would be a middle ground between making covopts too easy to spot and too difficult to spot.\r\n\r\nI'd favor the first option as I find covops way too easy to spot, but this is indeed a gameplay change.\r\n\r\nEdit: added option 3. ",
